  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (configuration gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver exposes three tunable configuration parameters — base mesh size (target cell count), near-wall y+ threshold, and hemolysis power-law exponent scaling factor — that materially affect predicted RH values. Validation studies were conducted at the analyst-chosen settings documented in the validation report narrative; however, no configuration-binding node links those settings to the deployment model, and the Context of Use does not constrain which parameter values must be used during regulatory submission runs.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "conformsToProfile_cou": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileComplete",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
