      "name": "Mesh convergence study at analyst-chosen base cell count",
      "description": "Grid refinement study performed at three mesh densities (coarse: 1.2M cells, medium: 3.8M cells, fine: 9.1M cells) using the base mesh size parameter set to the analyst-chosen value of 3.8M cells for production runs. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI < 2.1% for RH at all five operating points. Results reported at the chosen settings; no configuration node pins the base mesh size parameter for deployment use.",
      "quantitativeResult": "GCI_max = 2.08%, RH_fine/RH_medium ratio = 1.014 across 5 operating points",
      "assessedFactorType": "Discretization error"
    },
