      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Near-wall y+ threshold sensitivity at validation settings",
      "description": "Sensitivity of predicted wall shear stress and hemolysis index to near-wall y+ threshold evaluated at y+ target values of 1, 5, and 30. Validation concluded that y+ ≤ 5 is required for RH accuracy within 8% of experimental benchmark. All validation runs used y+ = 1 as the chosen setting. The y+ threshold is not bound in any deployment configuration document; an analyst deploying the model could select y+ = 30 without triggering a configuration violation check.",
      "quantitativeResult": "RH deviation: y+=1 vs experiment: 4.2%; y+=5: 7.8%; y+=30: 23.1%",
      "assessedFactorType": "Numerical solver error"
    },
    {
