      "name": "Hemolysis power-law exponent scaling factor validation",
      "description": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model includes a user-adjustable scaling factor (alpha) that modulates the magnitude of predicted hemolysis index. Validation studies used alpha = 1.0 (unscaled). Sensitivity analysis indicates RH varies by ±31% across the plausible range alpha ∈ [0.7, 1.3]. The validation report narrative states results were obtained 'at the chosen settings (alpha = 1.0)' but no bindsConfiguration link or settings node records this value as a deployment constraint. The Context of Use is silent on permissible alpha values.",
